This place was nice. Best described as a boutique bowling alley. There was good music, a decent menu, and good drinks. We had a party of approx. 12-15 people. We  purchased multiple drink and a plethora of food.  However, the waitress assigned to our group was lackluster and dry. It appeared she was not a happy camper and at times annoyed. When I say we ordered a lot of stuff,  I mean a lot. I would estimate 15+ drinks and 15 different items from the menu. Cha-ching!!!!! Yet, she remained underwhelming, despite our pleseant demeanor. I would suggest getting staff that are excited to be at such a fun place. It appeared to be a slow night too. Therefore, she should of embrace the parrons present. Double and triple orders of food, the spinach dip, wings, brussel sprouts, fries, fried okra, sliders, and tacos were good. However, the spring rolls were sent back, they were awful, even for the vegitarian in the group, and by the way there is a diference in peanuts sauce and smearing peanut butter on the plate....thumbs down!!! The menu variety was appreciated. In closing, great location, the validated parking was an incentive ($5) and the atmosphere was inviting. Though we did not utilize the pool table and bar, they were noted.
